# Keep the build context small and stable so edits to non-build files don't
# invalidate Docker layers. Nothing excluded here is a Go build input
# (no go:embed of these paths; services resolve `shared` via replace directives).

.git
.gitignore

# Secrets — never copy into any build layer (the go-builder base does `COPY . .`,
# and base images may be pushed to a registry).
.env
.env.*
*.env
.jwt_secret
**/*.pem
**/*.key

# Tests are never compiled by `go build .`, and editing one should not bust the
# build cache (running `go test` happens on the host, not in the image build).
**/*_test.go

# Runtime data / generated output — never part of a build.
**/uploads/
**/outputs/
files/

# Docs, API collections, and helper scripts — not build inputs.
# NOTE: do NOT exclude deployment/backup/ — the db-backup image COPYs
# deployment/backup/backup.sh (see deployment/backup/Dockerfile).
docs/
postman/
scripts/
**/*.md

# OS / editor cruft
**/.DS_Store
